60.1	Legionellosis	Legionellosis	Legionellosis is a potentially fatal infectious disease caused by gram negative, aerobic bacteria belonging to the genus Legionella. Over 90% of legionellosis cases are caused by Legionella pneumophila, a ubiquitous aquatic organism that thrives in temperatures between 25 and 45 °C (77 and 113 °F), with an optimum temperature of .	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Legionella_pneumophila_%28SEM%29.jpg/220px-Legionella_pneumophila_%28SEM%29.jpg
